trans-unit.source: We know you’ve been waiting a while for an answer to your question, and we’d like to thank you for your patience. We just want to let you know that not all questions on HealthTap receive answers. A question is likely to go unanswered if it lacks detail, the question is unclear, or if it contains terms with which the doctors are not familiar. We are writing to let you know that your question is much more likely to receive a response if you improve it by editing or resubmitting it.

trans-unit.source: Questions must include enough detail to be meaningful and answerable. Vague questions that name a topic (for example, “I have a discharge”) without asking something specific are hard to answer. Try to mention whether the question is about a man or a woman, whether the topic relates to a certain age group, how long ago the symptoms started, and which parts of the body are affected.

target.mrk: La preguntas deben incluir detalles suficientes para ser significativas y respondibles.
